title: Matchsafe, "Figure of Punch", late 19th century
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
creditline: Gift of Stephen W. Brener and Carol B. Brener
description: In the shape of the character Punch shown from the waist up, with long nose and chin, wearing a pointed cap, hands joined together at his front, identical front and reverse. Circular opening at base, hinged at back. Striker on bottom.

tombstone.epitaph:
Matchsafe, "Figure of Punch", late 19th century.
late 19th century. Plated brass. Gift of Stephen W. Brener and Carol B. Brener. 1982-23-626.
